    "View as trajectories: present data chronologically to show which topics are discussed, the sentiment of views expressed or the emotions detected.",
    "This is a good place to begin to see patterns and areas of interest in the data.Presenting longitudinal data as a trajectory is advocated by [87] and complements how trends can be seen quickly through real-time data collection [97]. 3.",
    "Human review: according to similar studies [98,99], it is important to human review a sample of the tweets.",
    "This offers us the opportunity to not only classify the tweets according to the categories defined by each tool but also annotate instances of potential inaccuracy, such as sarcasm or negation.",
